66
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:42,600
There's a phone number

67
00:04:42,600 --> 00:04:46,600
555-8448.

68
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:50,600
Robbie, maybe you should call them Robbie

69
00:04:50,600 --> 00:04:53,600
and tell the Levinsons we have their cute little spaniel.

70
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:55,600
I've always wanted a springer spaniel.

71
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:57,600
She's so cute.

72
00:04:57,600 --> 00:05:20,600
The number you are calling "555-8448"

73
00:05:20,600 --> 00:05:23,600
is no longer in service.

74
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:27,600
The number's no longer in service.

75
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:33,600
Oh, you poor, poor baby.

76
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:34,600
You've lost your family.

77
00:05:34,600 --> 00:05:36,600
We'll find them.

78
00:05:36,600 --> 00:05:37,600
Don't worry, Alexandra.

79
00:08:27,600 --> 00:08:30,600
Don't worry, Alexandra.

80
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:31,600
We'll find the owner.

81
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:32,600
How, Robbie?

82
00:08:32,600 --> 00:08:34,600
Let me think.

83
00:08:34,600 --> 00:08:36,600
Gemma, sit.

84
00:08:36,600 --> 00:08:37,600
Good Gemma.

85
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:38,600
Give me your paw.

86
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:40,600
Good Gemma.

87
00:08:40,600 --> 00:08:41,600
This dog is well trained.

88
00:08:41,600 --> 00:08:43,600
She likes you, too.

89
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:45,600
So how are we going to find the owners?

90
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:47,600
With a little help from the ASPCA,

91
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:52,600
the American Society for the Prevention of Cruelty to Animals.

92
00:08:52,600 --> 00:08:53,600
They're the ones.

93
00:08:53,600 --> 00:08:55,600
We once found a cat.

94
00:08:55,600 --> 00:08:57,600
She was caught in the branches of our tree.

95
00:08:57,600 --> 00:08:58,600
And Dad called the ASPCA.

96
00:08:58,600 --> 00:09:00,600
They came and solved the problem.

97
00:09:00,600 --> 00:09:02,600
Robbie, let's call them.

98
00:09:02,600 --> 00:09:09,600
Let me see. ASPCA...

99
00:09:09,600 --> 00:09:15,600
Here it is.

100
00:09:15,600 --> 00:09:17,600
ASPCA Animal Shelter.

101
00:09:17,600 --> 00:09:22,600
555-7700.

102
00:09:22,600 --> 00:09:35,600
(beep...)

103
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:38,600
Hello, ASPCA.

104
00:09:38,600 --> 00:09:41,600
Hello, my name is Robbie Stewart.

105
00:09:41,600 --> 00:09:43,600
I have a lost dog I'd like to bring to you.

106
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:45,600
How late are you open?

107
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:46,600
We're open till nine P.M.

108
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:47,600
Thank you.

109
00:09:47,600 --> 00:09:49,600
I'll bring the dog over by nine.

110
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:50,600
Thanks.

111
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:50,600
Bye.

112
00:09:50,600 --> 00:09:51,600
Thanks.

113
00:09:51,600 --> 00:09:52,600
Good-bye.

114
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:01,600
They're still open?

115
00:10:01,600 --> 00:10:02,600
They're open until nine o'clock.

116
00:10:02,600 --> 00:10:04,600
We have two and a half hours.

117
00:10:04,600 --> 00:10:06,600
Let's take Gemma by there now.

118
00:10:06,600 --> 00:10:07,600
They'll find the owner.

119
00:10:07,600 --> 00:10:09,600
I hope so.

120
00:10:09,600 --> 00:10:13,600
I'm so sad to see this little dog without her family.

121
00:10:13,600 --> 00:10:15,600
I'm sure they'll find the owner.

122
00:10:15,600 --> 00:10:18,600
But if they don't, I'll adopt her.

123
00:10:18,600 --> 00:10:20,600
She's so cute.

124
00:10:20,600 --> 00:10:24,600
Look at those eyes.

125
00:10:24,600 --> 00:10:26,600
She's hard to resist.

126
00:10:26,600 --> 00:10:28,600
Don't you just love her?

127
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:32,600
I'd like to keep her, too.

128
00:10:32,600 --> 00:10:34,600
But I'll be going home to Greece

129
00:10:34,600 --> 00:10:36,600
at the end of the semester.

130
00:10:36,600 --> 00:10:39,600
She just wants love and affection.

131
00:10:39,600 --> 00:10:44,600
Come on, Robbie.

132
00:10:44,600 --> 00:10:45,600
Let's get her to the animal shelter,

133
00:10:45,600 --> 00:10:47,600
so they can find her owners quickly.

134
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:49,600
Don't worry, Gemma.

135
00:10:49,600 --> 00:10:51,600
We'll get you home.

136
00:10:51,600 --> 00:10:53,600
It's not easy being away from home.

137
00:10:53,600 --> 00:10:55,600
Come on, poochie.

138
00:10:55,600 --> 00:10:56,600
Atta girl!

139
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:58,600
Let's go.

140
00:10:58,600 --> 00:11:01,600
We're off to the animal shelter.

141
00:11:01,600 --> 00:11:24,600
let's thank taotao

142
00:11:24,600 --> 00:11:25,600
Your name?

143
00:11:25,600 --> 00:11:26,600
Robbie Stewart.

144
00:11:26,600 --> 00:11:28,600
And this is Alexandra Pappas.

145
00:11:28,600 --> 00:11:31,600
Your name will do, Mr. Stewart.

146
00:11:31,600 --> 00:11:35,600
Your address?

147
00:11:35,600 --> 00:11:39,600
46 Linden street, Riverdale.

148
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:43,600
Where did you find the dog?

149
00:11:43,600 --> 00:11:45,600
She found us.

150
00:11:45,600 --> 00:11:47,600
You tried calling the number on the collar?

151
00:11:47,600 --> 00:11:50,600
Yes, but the number's no longer in service.

152
00:11:50,600 --> 00:11:53,600
And there's no address on the dog tag?

153
00:11:53,600 --> 00:11:55,600
There's no other information.

154
00:11:55,600 --> 00:11:57,600
No ID number.

155
00:11:57,600 --> 00:12:00,600
Without that, it's hard.

156
00:12:00,600 --> 00:12:03,600
You will try to find the dog's owner.

157
00:12:03,600 --> 00:12:05,600
Oh, we'll try, believe me.

158
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:08,600
And if you don't?

159
00:12:08,600 --> 00:12:09,600
Yes?

160
00:12:09,600 --> 00:12:14,600
If you don't... can I... can I adopt the dog?

161
00:12:14,600 --> 00:12:15,600
Why, yes.

162
00:12:15,600 --> 00:12:18,600
If the owners don't claim the dog in 48 hours,

163
00:12:18,600 --> 00:12:20,600
then you can apply for adoption.

164
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:21,600
How do I do that?

165
00:12:21,600 --> 00:12:23,600
You really want to?

166
00:12:23,600 --> 00:12:24,600
Yes, I'm serious.

167
00:12:24,600 --> 00:12:27,600
If no one comes to claim Gemma,

168
00:12:27,600 --> 00:12:28,600
I'd like to adopt her.

169
00:12:28,600 --> 00:12:30,600
It's not difficult.

170
00:15:52,600 --> 00:15:55,600
OK.

171
00:15:55,600 --> 00:15:58,600
If you want to adopt an animal,

172
00:15:58,600 --> 00:16:00,600
first we need to know some references.

173
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:02,600
References?

174
00:16:02,600 --> 00:16:04,600
People we know?

175
00:16:04,600 --> 00:16:07,600
Friends, teachers...

176
00:16:07,600 --> 00:16:09,600
We need to talk to some people about you.

177
00:16:09,600 --> 00:16:12,600
We want to be sure that you're responsible

178
00:16:12,600 --> 00:16:14,600
and that you can take good care of an animal.

179
00:16:14,600 --> 00:16:17,600
Then you have to fill out this form

180
00:16:17,600 --> 00:16:18,600
about your family background.

181
00:16:18,600 --> 00:16:20,600
Is that it?

182
00:16:20,600 --> 00:16:22,600
No, there's more.

183
00:16:22,600 --> 00:16:26,600
We need to know about your history with animals.

184
00:16:26,600 --> 00:16:27,600
Have you ever owned an animal?

185
00:16:27,600 --> 00:16:28,600
Yes.

186
00:16:28,600 --> 00:16:31,600
We had a cat when I was eight years old.

187
00:16:31,600 --> 00:16:32,600
I love cats.

188
00:16:32,600 --> 00:16:34,600
Do you have any animals now?

189
00:16:34,600 --> 00:16:36,600
Unfortunately, no.

190
00:16:36,600 --> 00:16:38,600
Anything else?

191
00:16:38,600 --> 00:16:39,600
We also like to know

192
00:16:39,600 --> 00:16:41,600
your reasons for wanting an animal.

193
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:44,600
Just to hold it and cuddle with it.

194
00:16:44,600 --> 00:16:46,600
Just to have as a pet.

195
00:16:46,600 --> 00:16:47,600
I love animals.

196
00:16:47,600 --> 00:16:52,600
To have a friend - a pal.

197
00:16:52,600 --> 00:16:55,600
You know, man's best friend is his dog.

198
00:16:55,600 --> 00:16:58,600
And one thing more.

199
00:16:58,600 --> 00:17:00,600
If you're under 21 years of age...

200
00:17:00,600 --> 00:17:01,600
That's me.

201
00:17:01,600 --> 00:17:02,600
Then an adult must sign for you.

202
00:17:02,600 --> 00:17:03,600
Uh-oh.

203
00:17:03,600 --> 00:17:05,600
No problem.

204
00:17:05,600 --> 00:17:07,600
My parents will think it's a good idea.

205
00:17:07,600 --> 00:17:09,600
I'll be back with them.

206
00:17:09,600 --> 00:17:11,600
If the real owners don't come to claim Gemma...

207
00:17:11,600 --> 00:17:13,600
After forty-eight hours.

208
00:17:13,600 --> 00:17:15,600
But please call first.

209
00:17:15,600 --> 00:17:19,600
Thanks for your information and for being so helpful.

210
00:17:19,600 --> 00:17:20,600
It's my pleasure.

211
00:17:20,600 --> 00:17:22,600
Nice talking to both of you.

212
00:17:22,600 --> 00:17:23,600
Thanks again.

213
00:17:23,600 --> 00:17:24,600
Bye.

214
00:17:24,600 --> 00:17:28,600
Maybe the real owners will come to claim her.

215
00:17:28,600 --> 00:17:30,600
Her eyes look so sad.

216
00:17:30,600 --> 00:17:32,600
She must really miss them.

217
00:17:32,600 --> 00:17:34,600
I see you're both animal lovers.

218
00:17:34,600 --> 00:17:35,600
We are.

219
00:17:35,600 --> 00:17:36,600
Good-bye, Miss Aborn.

220
00:17:36,600 --> 00:17:38,600
We'll call in a couple of days.

221
00:17:38,600 --> 00:17:40,600
Good-bye, and thanks for bringing Gemma in.

222
00:17:40,600 --> 00:17:42,600
Bye.

223
00:17:42,600 --> 00:17:55,600
I keep thinking about the dog, about Gemma,

224
00:17:55,600 --> 00:17:56,600
alone in the animal shelter.

225
00:17:56,600 --> 00:17:58,600
I know.

226
00:17:58,600 --> 00:18:00,600
But I promise you, Alexandra,

227
00:18:00,600 --> 00:18:02,600
the dog is just fine.

228
00:18:02,600 --> 00:18:04,600
They're very kind to the animals.

229
00:18:04,600 --> 00:18:05,600
I know they are.

230
00:18:05,600 --> 00:18:07,600
I mean about her being alone.

231
00:18:07,600 --> 00:18:09,600
Even if they are kind to Gemma,

232
00:18:09,600 --> 00:18:11,600
she's still alone, without her family.

233
00:18:11,600 --> 00:18:13,600
Ready, folks?

234
00:18:13,600 --> 00:18:14,600
Are you ready, Alexandra?

235
00:18:14,600 --> 00:18:16,600
Yes, I'm ready.

236
00:18:16,600 --> 00:18:18,600
I'll have the chef's salad, please.

237
00:18:18,600 --> 00:18:22,600
I will have a cheeseburger, medium rare,

238
00:18:22,600 --> 00:18:25,600
